<abstract><t>This document defines the HTTP Origin header.  The Origin header is added by the user agent to describe the security context that initiated an HTTP request.  HTTP servers can use the Origin header to defend themselves against Cross-Site Request Forgery (CSRF) attacks.</t></abstract>

